  <description><![CDATA[<p>Having been in the same family for four generations, the staff here create a welcoming atmosphere and many special touches, this also makes the Augustin the oldest family-run hotel in <a data-udi="umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/d517b2c21fa94eb096a3bcb6b7e933c5}" title="Bergen">Bergen</a>. Located in the harbour area of the city centre, making this hotel a convenient base to explore this fascinating city. Just a short walk from the harbour, fish market, international restaurants and the historic Bryggen Wharf.</p>
<p>The Augustin has a unique touch with both original paintings and sculptures created by Norwegian artists on display throughout the hotel. Guests can also enjoy the Augustin’s award-winning wine bar, Altona, which is located in the hotels 400-year old stone cellar. This is the perfect place to end your day of city sightseeing, or stop in the comfortable lounge area for complimentary tea and coffee.</p>]]></description>
